gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 101, Jazz 90
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Jazz, 101-90. Karl-Anthony Towns led Minnesota with 32 points, 11 rebounds, and four assists as Nickeil Alexander-Walker added 20 points, seven assists, and five rebounds. Collin Sexton (14 points, four assists, three rebounds) and Ochai Agbaji (13 points, six rebounds) led Utah. Minnesota has now won three in a row and improve to 14-4 on year as the Jazz move to 6-13.
